| Edge Case | How Handled |
|---|---|
| Listener removes itself mid-emit | Snapshot preserves iteration; self-removal updates main array but doesn't crash |
| Earlier listener removes a later one | Victim still in snapshot → may run (test explicitly permits this) |
| Unsubscribe called during emit | Same as above; "second" listener in snapshot still fires |
| `off()` on non-existent event/listener | `_removeListener` returns early, no throw |
| `once` after it fires not counted | Removed from Map before `entry.fn()` call |
| `emit` return value for `once` | Length checked before loop, so first emit always returns `true` |
| `eventNames()` after all listeners removed | Empty arrays are deleted from Map immediately in `_removeListener` |

